 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/5/01 10:16:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upgrades wanted, need help</span><hr size=1> For upgrades, the only ones I can suggest to you that would be easy would be ones that would cost plat.<br>
<br>
Ring: Velium Jasper rings x 2<br>
Face: Velium Ruby Veil<br>
Waist: Reed Belt (you can camp or buy it)<br>
Chest: Ruined Mithril Breastplate (+5 wis and decent AC and some STR I believe).<br>
Feet:  GEB's (golden effreeti boots), relatively easy to obtain, took me about three freeti raids to get these.<br>
Back:  Mammoth hide cloak (from perma) -&gt; decent stats.<br>
<br>
Those four will bring you over 200 wisdom and from here on in you should be able to keep your wisdom at 200 or over easily.<br>
<br>
The rest of the equipment I can suggest is semi-easy raid attainable equipment.  Since you are 47 you can go to the planes, but I would suggest getting 49 before actively going to the planes because the spells at 49 will help you get accepted a LOT easier.<br>
<br>
Wrist:  Vermiculated Bracer (one of the best peices of Druid equipment) -&gt; Try both Fear and Hate for these, I find they drop more in Hate off of chests, but /shrug<br>
<br>
Waist: Dwearmovine Garland (sp?) -&gt; drops off of tenticles in fear I believe I got mine from and I still wear it today.  It replaced my reed belt.  Semi easy to obtain as most druids there will pass that belt up or allready have in favour of getting in on Verm armor drops.<br>
<br>
Legs:  Kromriff Military Leggings, quest starts in Thurg I believe, good stats, you (at 49) and another person at level 50 can do this easily between you, you just really need help at the last part.<br>
<br>
After these upgrades the only ones I can suggest would be ones attainable easier by a 55+ druid as you would need to go to Kael for thurg quest armor or ToV for ss or Kael quest armor and do quests that are a LOT easier when you are 55+ or have a LOT of help whenever you need it.<br>
<br>
some upgrades once you are 55+ include Gladiator arms and legs (from Kael), Paebala BP (from DN), Coldain Skin gloves (dropable, quested from giant faction, but buyable), NWS (epic), Lodizal sheild...I could go on, but the first of these is the easier and all of these are close to end game for a druid.<br>
<br>
